e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That our planet, Earth, exists in what=
 astronomers call a Goldilocks Zone &#8211; just the right distance from th=
e Sun to be habitable &#8211; is one of a million factors that needed to go=
 just-right for us to be here, monkeys on the precipice of creating thinkin=
g machines.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>We are so lucky that I&#8217;ve wond=
ered whether </span><em>something</em><span> - god, a simulation creator, a=
 loving universe, capitalism, take your pick &#8211; wants to see us win. A=
s one of a billion examples of our fortune, I </span><a href=3D"https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/c0fe4e86-5577-4a6c-8ae7-0d6b5a4a806b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Q=
ifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">wrote</a><span> that the timing of =
the energy transition is almost too perfect: without the climate crisis, we=
 may have ended up in a much more devastating </span><em>energy</em><span> =
crisis.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There are those who believe our l=
uck is about to run out. Billions of years of evolution, poof, once we crea=
te AI that is better than us in every way. At best, we will be economically=
 useless passengers.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I don&#8217;t think that&#8=
217;s right. Humans are unimaginably lucky until proven otherwise, and beli=
eving that we are about to get luckier than ever just requires believing in=
 straight lines on a graph.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Look, I&#8217;m too dumb t=
o grok all of the cutting edge AI research papers, and I&#8217;m not deep i=
n the weeds of the AI conversation. This is just my left curve outsider com=
mon sense take, based on good ol&#8217; fashioned human intuition, and much=
 smarter people than me may disagree.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>I&#8=
217;m going to make the case that the data points to an </span><strong>AI G=
oldilocks Zone</strong><span>: with assistants that continue to get more an=
d more capable the more data and compute we feed them, and that have absolu=
tely no desire or ability to overtake us.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
><strong>AI is more like Oil than God. </strong><span>It&#8217;s an economi=
cally useful commodity that can be scaled and refined to act as a multiplie=
r on everything we do. Gasoline didn&#8217;t replace the horse and buggy; i=
t let buggies carry humans further, faster.&#160;&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">If AI is God, governments should lock it down. But if it&#8217;s =
Oil, they should do everything they can to promote its development and unle=
ash their countries&#8217; entrepreneurial vigor on refining it into more a=
nd more useful products.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If AI is God, you may a=
s well just give up. But if it&#8217;s Oil, you can celebrate each advance =
as another tool at your disposal, and plan for the very real disruptions an=
d opportunities those advances will inevitably create.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">Believing AI will become God is nihilistic. Believing it is Oil is o=
ptimistic.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>This whole rabbit hole started =
a couple weeks ago with another Goldilocks Zone of sorts. I had the rare lo=
ng drive with the kids asleep in the backseat and without Puja in the front=
=2E If she&#8217;d been there, she neve=
r would have let me listen to four hou=
rs of </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/b388410d-0acc-4e96-a9=
32-8cb36d84c5c3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">=
