: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">He predicted that music str=
eaming would come in 1999 or 2000. Napster arrived in 1999.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">In that 2012 post, he tracked millions of instructions per seco=
nd (MIPS) over time to predict that:&#160;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-l=
eft: 4px solid #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margi=
n-left: 20px;"><em>When will a general purpose computer be able to simulate=
 human level intelligence?</em><span> Between 2024 and 2050, depending on w=
hich estimate of the complexity of human intelligence is selected, and the =
number of computers used to simulate it.&#160;</span></p></blockquote><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;"><span>And, depending on which estimate of the complexity of hu=
man intelligence you select, he pretty much nailed it. Whether or not AI </=
span><em>is </em><span>intelligent, GPT-4 (2023) does a pretty damn good jo=
b of </span><em>simulating </em><span>it.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
>Hertling described the three simple steps he uses to predict the future (e=
mphasis mine):</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Step 1: Calculate the annual increa=
se</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Step 2: Forecast the linear trend</em></p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em><strong>Step 3: Mapping non-linear events to linear t=
rend</strong></em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In other words, plot the annual inc=
reases that have happened so far, extrapolate those increases out into the =
future, and then predict what new capabilities are possible at various futu=
re points.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s exactly what Leopold did=
