ong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Seven years ago, </span>=
<a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/af5092ee-06a1-41bf-a9f3-2060430a43=
79?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel =
style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Kevin Kelly w=
rote</a><span>, &#8220;Intelligence is not a single dimension, so &#8216;sm=
arter than humans&#8217; is a meaningless concept.&#8221; It bears repeatin=
g.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">GPT-4 is a Smart High Schooler on one =
dimension, and a bottom centile High Schooler on others. It&#8217;s dangero=
us to assume that strengthening the strong dimension will strengthen the ot=
hers. No A+ physics student ever became the star quarterback by becoming an=
 A++ physics student.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Kelly even anticipated the=
 Leopold chart, writing:&#160;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px sol=
id #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px=
;"><em><strong>Most technical people tend to graph intelligence the way Nic=
k Bostrom does in his book, Superintelligence &#8212; as a literal, single-=
dimension, linear graph of increasing amplitude.</strong><span> At one end =
is the low intelligence of, say, a small animal; at the other end is the hi=
gh intelligence, of, say, a genius&#8212;almost as if intelligence were a s=
ound level in decibels&#8230;</span></em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: =
20px;"><em><strong>The problem with this model is that it is mythical, like=
 the ladder of evolution.</strong></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">T=
hat&#8217;s not to say the Smell Test version of AGI and ASI will never hap=
pen &#8211; I&#8217;m sure they will at some point on some path &#8211; jus=
t that it seems like we&#8217;ll need new paths to get there, and that thos=
e may be much further away.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Put another =
way, you can believe that solar is going to continue to get much cheaper an=
d more abundant without believing that solar panels will start producing fu=
sion reactions themselves.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This might s=
ound like an overly pessimistic take coming from me, but it&#8217;s one of =
the most optimistic things I&#8217;ve ever written.&#160;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">If I&#8217;m right, we&#8217;re going to end up in the Goldilocks Zone =
once again.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-=
appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webk=
